+Loome skripti failiks nimega backup_script.sh.

#!/bin/bash

# Define variables
SOURCE_DIR="/home/boss"
DEST_DIR="/mnt/backup"
BACKUP_INTERVAL=300  # 5 minutes

# Function to create a backup
create_backup() {
    TIMESTAMP=$(date +'%Y%m%d_%H%M%S')
    BACKUP_FILE="${DEST_DIR}/backup_${TIMESTAMP}.tar.gz"
    tar -czf "$BACKUP_FILE" -C "$SOURCE_DIR" .
    echo "Backup created at $BACKUP_FILE"
}

# Infinite loop to create backups every 5 minutes
while true; do
    create_backup
    sleep $BACKUP_INTERVAL
done

+Teeme skripti käivitatavaks:

chmod +x backup_script.sh

+Vormindamine (eeldades, et ketas on /dev/sdb1)

sudo mkfs.ext4 /dev/sdb1

+Ühendamine
sudo mount /dev/sdb1 /mnt/backup

+Et veenduda, et ketas ühendatakse automaatselt ka pärast süsteemi taaskäivitust, lisage see /etc/fstab faili:
echo "/dev/sdb1 /mnt/backup ext4 defaults 0 2" | sudo tee -a /etc/fstab
